@startuml CIM_Only_Workflow
title CIM-Only Workflow Sequence Diagram

actor User as User
participant "gen_aasx\n:5002" as AASService
participant "cim_to_aas_algorithm" as CIMConverter
participant "CIM EQ XML" as CIM_EQ
participant "CIM GL XML" as CIM_GL
participant "AAS JSON File" as AASFile
participant "basyx-aas-env\n:8081" as AASEnv
participant "basyx-aas-registry\n:8082" as AASRegistry

User -> AASService: POST /api/generate-cim-aas\n{workflow: "cim_only",\ncim_eq_path: "...EQ_.xml",\ncim_gl_path: "...GL_.xml"}
activate AASService

AASService -> CIMConverter: processing_gen_aasx()\n(cim_eq_path, cim_gl_path)
activate CIMConverter

CIMConverter -> CIM_EQ: Parse CIM EQ XML
activate CIM_EQ
CIM_EQ --> CIMConverter: EQ Data
deactivate CIM_EQ

CIMConverter -> CIM_GL: Parse CIM GL XML\n(Location data)
activate CIM_GL
CIM_GL --> CIMConverter: GL Data
deactivate CIM_GL

CIMConverter -> CIMConverter: Build hierarchical AAS structure\n- Create AAS for each asset type\n- Create Netzlokation/Messlokation\n- Build BoM hierarchies\n- Add bidirectional CIM references

CIMConverter -> AASFile: Write enhanced AAS JSON\ncim_eq_gl_aasx_hierarchical_*.json
activate AASFile
AASFile --> CIMConverter: File written
deactivate AASFile

CIMConverter --> AASService: Conversion result\n{output_file: "...json", aas_count: X, submodel_count: Y}
deactivate CIMConverter

AASService -> AASService: Auto-register with BaSyx

AASService -> AASEnv: POST /shells\n(AAS registration)
activate AASEnv
AASEnv --> AASService: 201 Created / 200 OK
deactivate AASEnv

AASService -> AASRegistry: PUT /shell-descriptors\n(AAS descriptor registration)
activate AASRegistry
AASRegistry --> AASService: 200 OK
deactivate AASRegistry

AASService --> User: 200 OK\n{success: true, workflow: "cim_only",\nresults: {cim_conversion: {...},\nbasyx_registration: {...}}}
deactivate AASService

@enduml